read_ilm_eco_db(25.10)                                  read_ilm_eco_db(25.10)

Name
       read_ilm_eco_db

Syntax
       read_ilm_eco_db

       [-help]

       {-dir <directoryName> | -module_model_tag <tagName>}

       Reads  an  ECO  file  after restoring a block-level design for non-iHDB
       flow.

              * For iHDB flow, you should  use  restore_module_model  -add_ons
                {eco}  command  to read the ECO file. Internally, restore_mod-
                ule_model  -add_ons  {eco}  will  source    <cellName>_eco.tcl
                script  that internally calls the read_ilm_eco_db -module_mod-
                ule_tag command.

              * For  non-iHDB  flow,  if  you   use   write_ilm_eco_db   -mod-
                ule_model_tag,    you   should   use   read_ilm_eco_db   -mod-
                ule_model_tag to read an ECO file at block-level design.

       Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description of the read_ilm_eco_db command.  For
              a detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man read_ilm_eco_db

       -dir <directoryName>
              Specifies the directory name to write the ILM eco database.

              At  the  block-level  design, if you use this command to read in
              the ECO changes, the command will automatically find  out  about
              the  design  name  and only load/read the ECO file for this spe-
              cific design.

       -module_model_tag <tagName>
              Specifies the tag name to use for iHDB.

              Use this option if write_ilm_eco_db -module_model_tag is used to
              save ECO file(s).

Related Information
              * restore_module_model

              * write_ilm_eco_db

